article.description: Jordon Varnado and Wesley Person each scored 14 points and Troy held on for a 65-63 victory over Hawaii on Friday night.
article.headline: Troy escapes with a 65-63 win over Hawaii
article.linkText: Troy escapes with a 65-63 win over Hawaii
article.story: HONOLULU -- Jordon Varnado and Wesley Person each scored 14 points and Troy held on for a 65-63 victory over Hawaii on Friday night. Hawaii forward Gibson Johnson had a steal and assisted on Noah Allen's fast-break layup to tie it at 60-all. But Alex Hicks hit two free throws to give Troy a 62-60 lead and after Hawaii missed a 3, DeVon Walker was fouled in the backcourt and hit two free throws to extend the lead to 64-60. Johnson was fouled under the basket on an inbound pass with 1:06 left. He missed the second of two free throws, but it went out of bounds off of Troy and his jumper made it 64-63. Kevin Baker made 1 of 2 at the stripe with 4 seconds left and Allen's driving attempt was off the mark. Hicks finished with nine points and six rebounds for Troy (3-3), which scored the first 16 points of the game. Jack Purchase led Hawaii (3-3) with a career-high 21 points after making 6 of 11 3-pointers.
